comment: Yesterday's air was moderate but it's looking better today, though you may want to keep an eye on those forecasts.
The air in Gilgit is currently unhealthy for sensitive groups, but the forecast suggests a transition to good air quality tomorrow.
The air in Skardu is "Moderate" today - not too bad, but sensitive groups should still limit outdoor activities.
The air quality in Islamabad is currently "Unhealthy for Sensitive Groups," but looking to improve to "Moderate" tomorrow, so it's time to stock up on masks and wait for the autumn breeze.
The air in Abbottabad is moderate today, but tomorrow's forecast suggests a slight decline, so sensitive groups should plan to limit outdoor activities.
Dera Ismail Khan's air quality is currently Unhealthy, with PM2.5 and AQI levels exceeding safe limits, though tomorrow's forecast shows a potential improvement to Unhealthy for Sensitive Groups.

The air quality in Haripur has moved from moderate to unhealthy for sensitive groups, but the forecast suggests a return to safer levels tomorrow - just don't forget to avoid venturing outside if you're prone to irritation.
The air quality in Mohmand Agency is moderate and slightly worse than yesterday, but still safe for most people to enjoy the pleasant 25°C temperatures.
The air in Peshawar is unhealthy today, but the forecast suggests a welcomed return to moderate levels tomorrow - time to open those windows and let in some fresh (and breathable) air!
Faisalabad's air is currently in the "Very Unhealthy" range, though it may improve to "Unhealthy" tomorrow, so enjoy those indoor pursuits while you can!
The air in Lahore is currently very unhealthy but may improve to merely unhealthy tomorrow, so you might want to consider wearing a mask and staying indoors when possible.
The air quality in Mangla, Pakistan is currently "Unhealthy for Sensitive Groups" and likely to remain that way tomorrow, so time to stock up on those N95s.

Multan, Pakistan is dealing with some very unhealthy air today, but at least tomorrow's forecast looks slightly less dire - unless the weatherperson is just leaving tomorrow's air quality predictions up to chance.
Pindi Bhattian's air today is a bit spooky - PM2.5 levels are creeping into "very unhealthy" territory, but the forecast shows a glimmer of hope for clearer skies tomorrow.
The air in Rahim Yar Khan is currently very unhealthy, but the forecast suggests a promising improvement tomorrow if the hazy skies cooperate.
The air quality in Rawalpindi is currently Moderate, but the forecast suggests it may become Unhealthy for Sensitive Groups tomorrow.
The air in Sialkot is currently very unhealthy, but tomorrow's forecast suggests a welcome improvement to just unhealthy levels.
Yesterday's air in Karachi was "Moderate", but today's improvement to "Good" quality is a breath of fresh air - literally!
